# Build products of the bootstrap chain — regenerate via the B0 replay
# (REPLAY.md) and kaem/build-sr0i.sh. Vendored SOURCES are tracked; only the
# compiled outputs are ignored. The per-arch bin/ and artifact/ build dirs are
# also covered by stage0-posix's own upstream .gitignore files.
vendor/stage0-posix/AMD64/bin/
vendor/stage0-posix/AArch64/bin/
vendor/stage0-posix/riscv64/bin/
vendor/stage0-posix/x86/bin/
sr0i/sr0i
fasm/f_amd64
*.o
p1/arith-core.elf
vendor/boot2/**/*.o
*.img

# The vendored bootstrap SEED images are trust-root sources, not the emit *.img
# build outputs the `*.img` rule targets — keep them tracked.
!vendor/stage0-posix/bootstrap-seeds/**/*.img

# The AMD64 seed recipe (kaem.amd64) writes into ./AMD64/bin/ and ./AMD64/artifact/
# WITHOUT creating them; git can't store an empty dir, so a force-added .gitkeep in
# each keeps them present in a fresh clone (their contents stay ignored above).
